Step 2: Connect the EC2 Instance and run the following commands:
1. Switch to root user
- sudo -i
2. Update and upgrade system packages
- sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade -y
3. Install Docker sudo apt install
- docker.io -y
4. Run an Nginx container
- docker run -d --name container-nginx -p 3000:80 nginx
5. Run an Apache2 container
- docker run -d --name container-apache2 -p 3001:80 ubuntu/apache2
6. List all containers
- docker container ls -a
NOTE: inbound rule should be in all traffic
7. Copy the ipv4 and port (ipv4:port)
8. Now to stop, start, kill and prune, run the following commands:
- docker stop (container-Id)
- docker start (container-Id)
- docker kill (container-Id)
- docker container prune (container-Id)
